headline.main: ROOSEVELT IS BACK IN THE WHITE HOUSE; Arrives by Train From Miami, Where He Ended Long Air Journey From Morocco ROOSEVELT IS BACK IN THE WHITE HOUSE

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Jan. 31 -- President Roosevelt returned tonight to the White House, thus safely completing his history-making journey to North Africa, where with Prime Minister Winston Churchill he planned the future course of the war to end with the "unconditional surrender" of the Axis.
abstract: Casablanca conf: Roosevelt arrives, Wash; departure and arrival at Miami described
